        "questions": [
          "<h2 id=\"quick-quiz\">Quick quiz</h2>\n\n<p>Answer the three questions. There are hints to guide you to the correct answer.</p>\n\n<p>When you have answered each question, click on <strong>Check my answer</strong>.</p>\n\n<p>Have fun!</p>\n\n<form class=\"knowledge-quiz-question\">\n  <fieldset>\n    <legend>Question 1 of 3</legend>\n    <div class=\"knowledge-quiz-question__blurb\">\n      <p>In your project, you made an animation with a surprise. Click on the green flag to run the animation below, then run it again.</p>\n\n<div class=\"scratch-preview\" style=\"margin-left: 15px;\">\n  <iframe allowtransparency=\"true\" width=\"485\" height=\"402\" src=\"https://scratch.mit.edu/projects/embed/499932713/?autostart=false\" frameborder=\"0\"></iframe>\n</div>\n\n<p>Did you notice anything odd the second time? The surprise was ruined! What code block would you add to make the surprise work?</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"knowledge-quiz-question__answers\">\n    <div class=\"knowledge-quiz-question__answer\">\n<input type=\"radio\" name=\"answer\" value=\"1\" id=\"choice-1\" />\n<label for=\"choice-1\"><pre><code class=\"language-blocks3\">set size to (150) %\n</code></pre></label>\n</div>\n<div class=\"knowledge-quiz-question__answer\">\n<input type=\"radio\" name=\"answer\" value=\"2\" id=\"choice-2\" checked/>\n<label for=\"choice-2\"><pre><code class=\"language-blocks3\">switch costume to [egg-a v]\n</code></pre></label>\n</div>\n<div class=\"knowledge-quiz-question__answer\">\n<input type=\"radio\" name=\"answer\" value=\"3\" id=\"choice-3\" />\n<label for=\"choice-3\"><pre><code class=\"language-blocks3\">show\n</code></pre></label>\n</div>\n<div class=\"knowledge-quiz-question__answer\">\n<input type=\"radio\" name=\"answer\" value=\"4\" id=\"choice-4\" />\n<label for=\"choice-4\"><pre><code class=\"language-blocks3\">go to x: (75) y: (-100)\n</code></pre></label>\n</div>\n    </div>\n  </fieldset>\n  <ul class=\"knowledge-quiz-question__feedback\">\n  <li class=\"knowledge-quiz-question__feedback-item\" id=\"feedback-for-choice-1\">\n<p>The <strong>egg</strong> sprite is the correct size when you run the program again.</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"knowledge-quiz-question__feedback-item\" id=\"feedback-for-choice-2\">\n<p>Yes. You need to make the sprite switch to the correct costume (<strong>egg-a</strong>) when the project starts.</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"knowledge-quiz-question__feedback-item\" id=\"feedback-for-choice-3\">\n<p>You often need to remember to make a sprite show when the green flag is clicked, but in the project in the question, the <strong>egg</strong> sprite does show.</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"knowledge-quiz-question__feedback-item\" id=\"feedback-for-choice-4\">\n<p>The <strong>egg</strong> sprite does go to the correct starting position on the Stage.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n  <input type=\"button\" name=\"Submit\" value=\"submit\" />\n</form>\n\n",
          "<form class=\"knowledge-quiz-question\">\n  <fieldset>\n    <legend>Question 2 of 3</legend>\n    <div class=\"knowledge-quiz-question__blurb\">\n      <p>In your project, you controlled your animation with <code class=\"block3control\">wait</code> blocks.</p>\n\n<p>In this dinosaur project, you want the little dinosaur to wait 6 seconds before it pops out of the egg and surprises the big dinosaur.</p>\n\n<p><img src=\"https://projects-static.raspberrypi.org/projects/surprise-animation/6d0d6894b56114b786a89aae0c947a1774b9f753/en/images/quiz-q2.png\" alt=\"A dinosaur sprite and an egg sprite on the Stage.\" /></p>\n\n<p>Which script for the <strong>little dinosaur</strong> sprite would make this happen?</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"knowledge-quiz-question__answers\">\n    <div class=\"knowledge-quiz-question__answer\">\n<input type=\"radio\" name=\"answer\" value=\"1\" id=\"choice-1\" />\n<label for=\"choice-1\"><pre><code class=\"language-blocks3\">when this sprite clicked\nshow\n</code></pre></label>\n</div>\n<div class=\"knowledge-quiz-question__answer\">\n<input type=\"radio\" name=\"answer\" value=\"2\" id=\"choice-2\" />\n<label for=\"choice-2\"><pre><code class=\"language-blocks3\">when flag clicked\nshow\nwait [6] seconds\n</code></pre></label>\n</div>\n<div class=\"knowledge-quiz-question__answer\">\n<input type=\"radio\" name=\"answer\" value=\"3\" id=\"choice-3\" checked/>\n<label for=\"choice-3\"><pre><code class=\"language-blocks3\">when flag clicked\nwait [6] seconds\nshow\n</code></pre></label>\n</div>\n    </div>\n  </fieldset>\n  <ul class=\"knowledge-quiz-question__feedback\">\n  <li class=\"knowledge-quiz-question__feedback-item\" id=\"feedback-for-choice-1\">\n<p>This script needs user interaction for the little dinosaur to show.</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"knowledge-quiz-question__feedback-item\" id=\"feedback-for-choice-2\">\n<p>Here, the little dinosaur surprises the big dinosaur, and then waits 6 seconds.</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"knowledge-quiz-question__feedback-item\" id=\"feedback-for-choice-3\">\n<p>After 6 seconds, the little dinosaur appears and surprises the big dinosaur!</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n  <input type=\"button\" name=\"Submit\" value=\"submit\" />\n</form>\n\n",
          "<form class=\"knowledge-quiz-question\">\n  <fieldset>\n    <legend>Question 3 of 3</legend>\n    <div class=\"knowledge-quiz-question__blurb\">\n      <p>You created your animation by breaking it into parts and building it in the order in which it runs.</p>\n\n<p>Which order represents the animation that you made?</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"knowledge-quiz-question__answers\">\n    <div class=\"knowledge-quiz-question__answer\">\n<input type=\"radio\" name=\"answer\" value=\"1\" id=\"choice-1\" />\n<label for=\"choice-1\"><ul>\n  <li>\n    <p>Curiosity</p>\n  </li>\n  <li>\n    <p>Setup</p>\n  </li>\n  <li>\n    <p>Surprise!</p>\n  </li>\n</ul></label>\n</div>\n<div class=\"knowledge-quiz-question__answer\">\n<input type=\"radio\" name=\"answer\" value=\"2\" id=\"choice-2\" checked/>\n<label for=\"choice-2\"><ul>\n  <li>\n    <p>Setup</p>\n  </li>\n  <li>\n    <p>Curiosity</p>\n  </li>\n  <li>\n    <p>Surprise!</p>\n  </li>\n</ul></label>\n</div>\n<div class=\"knowledge-quiz-question__answer\">\n<input type=\"radio\" name=\"answer\" value=\"3\" id=\"choice-3\" />\n<label for=\"choice-3\"><ul>\n  <li>\n    <p>Setup</p>\n  </li>\n  <li>\n    <p>Surprise!</p>\n  </li>\n  <li>\n    <p>Curiosity</p>\n  </li>\n</ul></label>\n</div>\n    </div>\n  </fieldset>\n  <ul class=\"knowledge-quiz-question__feedback\">\n  <li class=\"knowledge-quiz-question__feedback-item\" id=\"feedback-for-choice-1\">\n<p>The ‘setup’ part resets your animation. It needs to come first so that your animation can be run again in the same way.</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"knowledge-quiz-question__feedback-item\" id=\"feedback-for-choice-2\">\n<p>Yes! You set up your sprites first, then created curiosity then ended with a surprise.</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"knowledge-quiz-question__feedback-item\" id=\"feedback-for-choice-3\">\n<p>Curiosity was not at the end of the animation. Something came afterwards.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n  <input type=\"button\" name=\"Submit\" value=\"submit\" />\n</form>\n\n"
